  "title": "Understanding Algorithm Complexity",
  "lessonText": "This lesson introduces the concept of algorithm complexity in Java.",
  "data": {
    "content": "- Algorithm complexity measures the efficiency of an algorithm.\n- It is often expressed in Big O notation.\n- Time complexity describes how the runtime of an algorithm increases with input size.\n- Space complexity refers to the amount of memory an algorithm uses.\n- Common complexities include O(1), O(n), O(n^2), and O(log n).\n- Understanding these concepts helps in selecting the right algorithm for a problem."
  }
}
